<p>brew install bison</p>

<p>go to icestorm website</p>

<p>Run all the the commands. like it says. Maybe youâ€™ll find more packages that you need installed that I had already. Look at the error and brew install some guesses.</p>

<p>Hereâ€™s a kicker, go into the makefile for the iceprog and add a 1 to the end of -lftdi so it becomes -lftdi1</p>

<p>I changed the Makefile in iceprog to have the following stuff. I donâ€™t think my libftdi was installing where expected by default</p>

<p>LDLIBS = -L/usr/local/lib -L/usr/lib -lftdi1 -lm
CFLAGS = -MD -O0 -ggdb -Wall -std=c99 -I/usr/include/libftdi1
DESTDIR = /usr/local</p>

<p>I guess cc automatically peels lib off the front. Go fig.</p>

